<item>
            <title>[SPR-834] No way to set listeners on the SessionFactory</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-834</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The LocalSessionFactory bean currently has no way to set listeners on the SessionFactory (via the Configuration.setListener) method.  This should as simple as accepting a map as a property of the LocalSessionFactoryBean, and when building the Configuration object, iterating through it, and calling Configuration.setListener on each iteration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
